The ruling APC got another shocker on Monday as a principal officer in in the House of Representatives was sacked  by the Appeal Court in Kaduna .
Majority Leader Alhassan Ado Dogwa who represents Tunduwada/Dogwa federal constituency was removed by the court presided over by Justice Oludotun Adefope Okojie.
The court ordered The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) to conduct a fresh election in the two local governments where the election took place.
Last week, the Appeal court also sacked Hon. Abdulmummin Jibrin, ordering  fresh election.

			
